Loucille F. Smith was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Loucille F. Smith was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Loucille F. Smith in court, in custody with Attorney Bradley J. Jansen.  Robert G. Barrington appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Initial appearance/Rights hearing has previously been held and there was request for Gov. Warrant at that time; Court notes the Gov. Warrant has now been filed for Def. to be extradicted to Maricopa County, Arizona; Atty. Jansen requests time to file Habeus Corpus; Atty. Jansen has now reviewed the statutes and will not be filing Habeus Corpus; Atty. Jansen notes Maricopa Co. demands her appearance there (has 4 months of credit); Court notes there is Gov. Warrant, makes findings and therefore Def. is ordered to be sent to State of Arizona; Court grants request for extradition; Def. to be given to officials from State of Arizona; Court signs Order; Def. remanded
